race.description: Brave Smash @ Yarraman Park CG&E Handicap
race.comment: OFF THE PRESS (8) exciting Canberra-trained gelding chasing his fourth win from his last five runs. Shouldered the 60kg with ease when holding them off for a tenacious nose win over 1250m at Randwick Kensington. Should handle the rise in class with winning apprentice staying aboard. Genuine top-three player. DASHING RUPERT (7) deep into his prep and due for a change of luck. Away slowly and held up in the straight when sixth over 1400m at Randwick Kensington. Value chance who can quickly return to form. SMASHING TIME (9) failed to bounce off his good third in BM78 class two-back, then seventh over 1200m here when no match for Axius last Saturday. Back in grade with the tongue-tie and winkers coming off. CROSS TASMAN (10) dug deep to score first up and this looks a logical stepping stone. Should roll forward from the deep and has to be included.
